node.text:
Happy Wednesday!
⠀
Your life coach & ambassador @daria_tsvenger is here 👐
⠀
Today I interviewed @aliyagrig - founder of @humancosmosapp - we talked about:
⠀
1. The power of consistency.
2. What it takes to support a person (and yourself) experiencing a mental health challenge.
3. Why we shouldn’t label ourselves.
4. How to love ourselves and why do we need it.
⠀
See you next Wednesday on our weekly LIVE ☀️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head in Austin, Texas with @aryanxmemes. May be an image of text that says 'Aryan @aryanxmemes Some people love to vibe alone. No dates, no besties, no parties. Just indoors with phone, laptop and good music. I'm some people.'.

node.text:
Tonight I’m some people. 

Lately, the more time I spend  alone the better I feel. I’m feeling overwhelmed by too much interaction with people, places and things. 

I need some down time. So here I am. 

What do you do when you’ve been too peopley? - @therealjoirizarry 

@aryanxmemes 
.
.
.
.
#extrovertedintrovert #downtime #metime💕 #timeforme❤️ #anxietysucks #mentalhealthmemes🖤 #safeplaceinsideyourhead

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head on July 23, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says '@oyerooh Yes love yourself. But also, analyze and be critical of how you think, act, and behave. Self love without self awareness is useless. Be accountable. 4/7/18, 10:37 AM'.

node.text:
I feel this strongly, for me I didn’t start on this mental health journey to help people until I helped myself. I used to be so terrible to people, I lied a lot, and always was ashamed that I didn’t come from an affluent background or look as in shape as my friends. Around the age of 18 I started holding myself accountable to being a better human being to people. I realized that being nice is free and the universe taking care of us is the price we get back. It’s hard to start change in self love, keep going I promise it’s worth it. Also I understand this advice won’t help everyone, I am just posting from personal experience. What are your thoughts? - @tanner_hamilton22 
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#accountability #selflove #selfcare #anxietyawareness #anxietyattack #howcanwehelp #becritical #movetheneedle #pleasekeepgoing #dontstopbelieving #asafeplaceinsideyourhead #youallarebeautiful

May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'MEFeaterCEO @GabrielleAmani Progress is the best feeling in the world Nick A @NickFolarin love posts like this. It shows realistic and relatable growth which often isn't shown on social media.'.

node.text:
Some days it’s the tiny things that add up to big progress. 

It might not be be glamorous or legendary but it’s still important.

Tag someone who you see making progress 👇🏼

We could all use a little a “hell yeah, you’re doing good” in our lives. - @therealjoirizarry 

@gabrielleamani 
@nickfolarin 

.
.
.
.
.
#progressnotperfection #itsthesimplethings #itsthesmallthings❤️ #thelittlethingsmatter #thelittlethingsadduptobigthings #mentalhealthmemes🖤 #mentalhealthadvocate👊 #weseeyou #youareseen #youredoinggreat #youredoinggood #improudofyou #anxietyrecovery #mentalhealthrecovery #safeplaceinsideyourhead

node.text:

.
.
.
.
.
.
#asafeplaceinsideyourhead #anxiety  #youareenough #keepgoing #imnotaloneright #mentalhealth #anxiety #beatanxiety #anxietyattack #anxietyawareness #ihopeimnotalone

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head on July 21, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Lethal LethalHomo Homo @LordeCali Thinking people should struggle because you did is very weird, miserable energy. 15:52 3/16/21 Twitter for iPhone'.

node.text:
My dad always compares struggles from back in the day to mine, and it drives me up a wall. It’s not a competition, no one wins, we all are just doing our best out here. The way my father compares things is so detrimental to my mental health, I’ve pretty much just tried to avoid actually telling him what’s wrong. Please do you best to respect everyone’s journeys. What you think is easy may be extremely difficult for someone else. Kindness goes a long way. - @tanner_hamilton22 
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#anxiety #comparisonisthethiefofjoy #westruggletogether #pleasekeepgoing #depression #anxiety #asafeplaceinsideyourhead #youallareamazing #anxietyattack #anxietyawareness #anxietyrelief #anxious

node.text:
We got a runner! 

Maybe subconsciously my obsession with become a runner is linked to this?  I do consider it a form of meditation since I can’t really think about anything else except for my damn breathing as I do it 😆

P.S. I had the courage to run my first 5K last Saturday. It took a lot of internal dialogue to get it done and external support from friends and family who virtually cheered me on. 

Any runners actually use it as therapy for your mental health issues? - @therealjoirizarry 
.
.
.
.
.
#runningawayfrommyproblems #itsdoesntactuallywork #runningastherapy #mentalhealthadvocate💚 #mentalhealthmemes🖤 #anxietyisreal #runningfromthetruth #asafeplaceinsideyourhead

node.text:
It’s tru tho! 

This just happened….I texted someone and the response is delayed. Surely they hate me or think I’m weird, right? 

It’s so hard to break this vicious cycle. How do you calm the hamster wheel in your 🧠? 

- @therealjoirizarry 
.
.
.
.
.
#overthinking #mybrainhurts #racingthoughts😣 #impostersyndrome #mentalhealth #mentalhealthmemes🖤 #anxietyproblems #hamsterwheelbrain #asafeplaceinsideyourhead

node.text:
Yeah…taking a day off from everything tomorrow. 

Phone off ☑️
Work laptop put away ☑️
Not opening any social media ☑️ 
Fading out of existence for 24 hrs ☑️

I think being realistic with those around you and letting them know your struggling helps…and in all honesty people I am struggling. Bad. I know this will pass but I want to be totally transparent with the community. Life is rough. - @tanner_hamilton22 
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#anxiety #anxietyrelief #howcanwehelp #asafeplaceinsideyourhead #beatdepressionandanxiety #beatanxiety #keepgoing #itgetsbetter #thisisrough #lifeiskickingmybutt

node.text:
I’ll practice this to say over and over again.

How many times has a person hurt you, whether they meant to or not, and you had to stop dead in your tracks and just not respond?

Sometimes I need the space to quiet and calm down the overwhelming hurt I’m feeling, so it’s just easier to step away. 

Look at me, adulting - @therealjoirizarry 

@mentalillnessquotesinfo 💚

Photo credit: @zapatistarising (twitter)💚

node.text:
Every day, I’m suffering, suffering 🥺

Toady I’ll try something new. I’ll reach past the suffering and into the healing. Th is feeling is temporary and I’ll replace it with feelings of gratitude and grace. 

It’s hard, but I can do it! - @therealjoirizarry 

@therapymemequeen
